NATION; 
CBS REPORTER ROBERT SCHAKNE DIES 
Robert Schakne, who covered stories for CBS News from Vietnam to Watergate and 
Three Mile Island to the Iran-Contra affair, died today in Washington. He was 
63. 
Schakne, who retired in July, 1988, was a 33-year veteran of CBS. He had been 
an investigative correspondent in the CBS News Washington bureau since 1976 and 
worked on such other major news stories as the investigation of the Challenger 
space shuttle disaster. He also covered the nuclear power industry on a regular 
basis. 
